pageContext.claim: “The job they did in the White House is unbelievable. There was never any form of like this sounds dangerous. All I could see is when I was seeing on television but they were outside and the Secret Service was incredible but we were also held by the DC police and we were helped by the National Guard was unbelievable.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump is wrong. A largely peaceful protest had formed outside the White House, which was broken up using forceful measures including gas in order for the president to take a photo in front of St. John's Episcopal Church.
